 We will set the issue of bases by writing the equation $2^x = 16$ and then solving for $x$ by raising both sides to the power of 0.5, \begin{align*}
2^{x\cdot \frac{1}{2}}&=2^{2\cdot \frac{1}{2}}\\
x&=2
\end{align*}
So, the integer $x=\boxed{2}$ satisfies the equation $2^{x+2}=32$.
